{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/4446", "repo": "rails", "body": "@ayamomiji hey, your fix looks correct but the test is passing by chance :). Sweepers / Observers are singletons, they will give you a NoMethodError if you call `new`, like this: \r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nNoMethodError: private method `new' called for AppSweeper:Class\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou can just go with the same approach as the other tests, something like:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nsweeper = ActionController::Caching::Sweeper.send(:new)\r\nassert_raise NoMethodError do\r\n  sweeper.send_not_defined\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen you can kill the `AppSweeper` class :). Could you review these before we merge, please? Thanks.", "_id": {"$oid": "523f17dabd354364b90154ca"}, "issue_id": 4446, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4794107", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/4446#issuecomment-4794107", "updated_at": "2012-03-28T23:48:58Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/r